    <h2 id="course-description">Course description</h2>

    <p>This course introduces students to the technical and workflow skills used by
    news application teams. Students will form into groups to conceive and execute
    a news project, along the way learning and applying best practices for team
    collaboration, goal-setting and project management.</p>

    <p>Students will also craft and execute individual learning plans designed
     to help them develop new technical skills and deepen mastery of existing skills. 
     These may range from the basics of web development using HTML, CSS and Javascript
     to more advanced skills such as using D3 and cloud services to create data-driven, 
     interactive graphics.</p>
     <p>Whatever the starting point, student learning plans must be aligned with their team's project goals.</p>

    <h2 id="course-format">Course format</h2>

    <p>Our classes will mainly serve as a venue for team planning and collaboration. This will include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Review of recent work</li>
      <li>Planning of next steps</li>
      <li>Pair coding and problem solving</li>
      <li>Review and alignment of learning goals with project-specific tasks</li>
      <li>Providing feedback on other team projects</li>
    </ul>

    <p>We'll also have occassional, brief lectures and discussions on topics related to news apps.</p>

    <h2 id="learning-objectives">Learning objectives</h2>

    <p>The primary goal will be to experience how news app developers work while building a news application, interactive graphics, and/or tools. Throughout the quarter, we'll focus on:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Collaborative workflows and tools</li>
      <li>Agile software development practices</li>
      <li>Project planning and management</li>
      <li>Setting, executing, and reflecting on goals</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="attendance">Attendance</h2>
