    <h2 id="grading-and-assignments">Grading and assignments</h2>
    <p>Grades will be based on the following criteria:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>The overall quality of the <strong>final team project</strong>, including but not limited to the effectiveness of visual communication, usability, and 
      alignment with news publication standards.</li>
      <li><strong>Individual contributions</strong> to the team project, including effective collaboration with teammates,  participation in team meetings, and code/technical contributions.</li>
      <li>The development and execution of <strong>individual learning plans </strong> (using SMART goals) aligned with team goals.</li>
      <li>Two <strong>"reflection" memos </strong>(at the half-way point and end of the quarter) on the progress of individual learning goals and the team project.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Below is an overview of the grading approach:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>A+</strong> ~ Exceeded course expectations and produced a project that meets the standards of a professional newsroom. Aggressively pushed the boundaries
      of current knowledge to acquire new skills and applied them in a way that helped the team achieve a high-quality project. Contributed to a high degree to the oveall
      success of the team project and other members of the team.</li>
      <li><strong>A</strong> ~ Met course expectations and produced a final project that <em>approaches</em> the level of quality expected in a professional newsroom. 
      Acquired new skills and/or refined pre-existing skills and used them to substantially contribute to the team's goals.</li>
      <li><strong>A- and lower</strong> ~ Failed to meet course expectations in one or more areas (personal skills development, team contributions, quality of final project).</li>
    </ul>

